Text.string: Got a dead guy here, Wainwright.
Wainwright, do you know this man who fell out of a closet?
This body was hiding in a closet. Wainwright, did you know this man?
Oi, get up, man.||—Wainwright? This fella's not gettin' up.

Why, that's Baldrin, our family butler! He knew where all the bodies were buried, and now it seems he's joined them. My father always suspected him of recording their conversations. See if he managed to capture his own untimely end.
Damn that harpy. What's that on their back?
An eviction notice? Seems Aurelia's clearin' house. Anyone who only got the axe metaphorically would have exited out through the cellar door. Go see if they left anything behind.
That pink slip is made out to one Clare Connorly. Why, I remember her—she was a dining attendant. Always kept my father's cup full. Track her down and see if she knows where the blackmail is stashed.
Aurelia? That icy BITCH fired me! Didn't even give me my back pay. All she offered me was this old-ass wine. Ugh. Tastes like freakin' cyanide!
You want dirt on her? I hid something out in the abandoned shack. Baldrin got some pretty ugly recordings before he got the icicle.
Aha! That statue was wearin' a wire! Appears that it was transmittin' its recordings to the safe nearby. It'll be triple locked, so find the three catches to open it up.
Wait, that was ACTUAL cyanide! Acccckclhrghrh.
Wow, heh! That thing you do with the ice is... wow. Are you, uh... sure you're not a Siren?
Ohohoho—no, nothing so magical. Just nanotech and years of experience. So, have we got a deal?

Oh, yeah, no, totally, uh—pff. We torture Montgomery Jakobs to death for the deed to his company, you find us his Vault Key, and, heh, you get to be a CEO. Gotta say, I'm surprised you'd pull one over on your brother. It seems kinda...
Cold? Troy, dear. You'll figure this out eventually—family is just another word for war. And the sister always wins. Now, show me again what you can do with your new powers.
Gladly, Baroness. Heh-heh-heh...

Eurgh. That harpy bedded that Siren ratboy and killed my father just to be richer than Alistair. I was feeling a bit lonely without any survivin' immediate family, but now I wonder if perhaps I'm better off. Bring that ECHO back to me.

Thank you, Vault Hunter. I can't imagine Alistair would want his sister's private indiscretions flaunted around—her public ones trouble him enough. I'll find a good place for this, such as a furnace, or some sort of large device that burns furnaces.
I know you've been recording me, Baldrin. Now, before I fire you, tell me—where did Montgomery Jakobs hide the Vault Key?

I haven't the faintest clue what you mean, Baroness. I have served four generations in Jakobs Manor with dignity and honor. And I intend to stay right here... unless you want it going public that you've gotten into bed with—HRK!
Sadly, we're in a bit of a hiring freeze at the moment.
Seems Baldrin was still a loyal servant, in his own way. If he did have blackmail against Aurelia, he'd have given it to the other staff for safekeepin'. Look in the servants' quarters.
